Package io.github.ljnelson.oci.secrets.configsource

Class ConfigurationBackedBuilderFunction

java.lang.Object
io.github.ljnelson.oci.secrets.configsource.ConfigurationBackedBuilderFunction
All Implemented Interfaces:
Function<String,GetSecretBundleRequest.Builder>
public final class ConfigurationBackedBuilderFunction extends Object implements Function<String,GetSecretBundleRequest.Builder>
A Function that, when supplied with a MicroProfile Config property name, returns a fully-configured GetSecretBundleRequest.Builder, or null if the property name is unsupported.

This class uses a user-supplied configuration facility to look up certain configuration values to supply to any GetSecretBundleRequest.Builder instances it may return from its apply(String) method.

Author:
Laird Nelson

  • Method Details

    • apply

      public final GetSecretBundleRequest.Builder apply(String propertyName)
      Returns a GetSecretBundleRequest.Builder suitable for the supplied propertyName, or null if the property name is unsuitable.

      If the supplied propertyName is null or blank, invocations of this method will return null.

      Otherwise, values for the following property names will be sought using the BiFunction supplied at construction time:

      • propertyName.opcRequestId
      • propertyName.secretId (required)
      • propertyName.secretVersionName
      • propertyName.stage
      • propertyName.versionNumber

      These values, if present, will be used to configure a GetSecretBundleRequest.Builder that will be returned.

      Specified by:
      apply in interface Function<String,GetSecretBundleRequest.Builder>
      Parameters:
      propertyName - the name of a property for which a GetSecretBundleRequest.Builder is to be returned; may be null in which case null will be returned
      Returns:
      a fully-configured GetSecretBundleRequest.Builder suitable for the supplied propertyName, or null
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if the supplied propertyName is non-null and not blank and a value for the propertyName.secretId property name is null or blank
      See Also:
      • GetSecretBundleRequest.Builder
